div2.p:
She turned her eyes now full upon me, and in her face I read an encouraging
                        sympathy. But she did not speak, and I, determined to make as good a defense
                        for myself as I could, went on:

"I am only a rebel, Kate, with a leave of absence from my command that will
                        expire in two hours, but I will help you if I can. Roger must not stay here;
                        if he is able let him go with me."

"Mr. Bellray," I began, "I want to say something about myself--ourselves;
                        something I have come a thousand miles to say. A part of it you already
                        know."
